cast cc on myself         : easy - /cast 6 (slot for cc)<br>
target nearest mob       : ??? (cant use F8 to my  <br>
                         knowledge or reprogram it seemingly)<br>
then reattack              : easy - /attack %t<br>
<br>
Freedance<br>
level 202 Paladin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulordcyke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lordcyke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/4/02 2:08:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Useful Macro Commands</span><hr size=1> Well in a group or raid situation it could work easily with a assist command.  Just set your assist to either the MA or Sa, or in group situation set your assist to another melee, chances are they will be on the same mob your fighting.  As for solo, guess your just going to have to reach up and use the f8 key.<br>
<br>
/target (self)<br>
/target (self)<br>
/cast 1-8 (where you have cc)<br>
/assist (MA's or other melee's name in group)<br>
<br>
I like to have two line targeting myself, due to lag and other issues, I would miss cc on myself, as it wouldn't taregt me fast enough.  Putting two lines in there is redundant, but never have any problems with missing after that.<br>
Depending how you have your assist set up, it will be autoattack, or because you've been fighting already attack should still be on.<br>
Can also add another ability like disarm, bash, or even but bash at the top, and my get lucky stun the mob, and not have to worry about an interupt...<br>
<br>
Other macro's I use<br>
<br>
Stun<br>
/cast 1 - quickest fasted reset (usually cease)<br>
/cast 2 - usual stun<br>
/cast 3 - usually holy might <br>
<br>
Abilities<br>
/Doability 1 - Bash<br>
/doability 2 - Taunt<br>
/doability 2 - Disarm<br>
/Cast 7 - Always yaulp IV<br>
- use this in group situations, when I want to agro as much as possible, and always cast yaulpV.<br>
<br>
Assist<br>
/assist (MA)<br>
/cast 7 - Always Yaulp<br>
<br>
LOH<br>
/target (self or important party member, only in risky situations)<br>
<br>
Some other one, many for certain situations...<br>
<br>
Cyke <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulordcyke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lordcyke</A> at: 6/4/02 2:17:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggorsmortus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RiggorsMortus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/smiley.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 376<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/4/02 6:31:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.standonguard.com/images/m_gordie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Useful Macro Commands</span><hr size=1> I like to put cast couple times to cover fizzles ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useventhsword.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seventhsword</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/5/02 5:49:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Useful Macro Commands</span><hr size=1> As for assist?  Commonly i'm returning to <br>
